				\begin{document}$${I}\propto {V}^{2}$$\end{document} (1.8 V–0.2 V). Subsequently, a linear relation is quickly observed between I and V. The conductive behavior obeys Ohmic conduction even though the bias reversely sweeps. When the device switches from LRS to HRS under VRESET\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
